ABSTRACT
The present invention discloses CloudCore_Sync_2, a revolutionary modular cybersecurity framework integrating artificial intelligence threat detection, quantum-safe protocols, and the novel Modular Input Trust Enforcement Layer (M.I.T.E.L.). This comprehensive platform addresses both digital and physical attack vectors through real-time threat intelligence, autonomous response coordination, and zero-trust peripheral device authentication. The invention represents a paradigm shift in cybersecurity by creating the first unified defense system capable of protecting against advanced persistent threats, social engineering attacks, hardware infiltration, and physical device spoofing across all computing platforms.

FIELD OF INVENTION
This invention relates to cybersecurity systems, specifically modular threat detection and response platforms incorporating artificial intelligence, quantum-safe cryptography, and physical device trust enforcement for comprehensive digital and hardware security protection.

BACKGROUND OF THE INVENTION
Current Cybersecurity Limitations
Modern cybersecurity solutions suffer from critical architectural flaws:

Fragmented Defense Systems: Current solutions operate in silos, creating security gaps between network, endpoint, and application layers.
Digital-Only Protection: Existing platforms ignore physical attack vectors including USB-based attacks, hardware keyloggers, and Point-of-Sale (POS) skimmers.
Reactive Response Models: Traditional systems detect threats after compromise, lacking predictive and preventive capabilities.
Limited AI Integration: Current AI implementations focus on pattern recognition rather than comprehensive threat intelligence and autonomous response.
Platform Dependency: Existing solutions lack true cross-platform compatibility, leaving mobile and embedded systems vulnerable.

Physical Attack Vector Gap
A critical vulnerability exists in peripheral device trust management:

USB Attack Tools: Devices like Rubber Ducky, OMG Cables, and USB HID emulators can inject malicious payloads instantly upon connection
POS Vulnerabilities: Card skimmers and spoofing adapters compromise payment systems at the hardware level
Zero-Trust Absence: No enterprise solutions implement proper zero-trust logic for connected peripherals
Authentication Gaps: Input devices operate without verification, enabling immediate payload injection

Market Need
The global cybersecurity market lacks a unified platform capable of:

Integrating AI-powered threat detection with physical device authentication
Providing real-time cross-platform protection from mobile to enterprise
Implementing zero-trust principles at both network and hardware levels
Offering autonomous threat response with quantum-safe communication


